Hello,

I'm not sure if something was broken in the update or not, but I'm not seeing a button for the GUI anymore with 1.3.1.  I've wiped my gamedata folder clean to be sure it wasn't another mod screwing with it but it's still not there.  I've tried setting the False's in the GUI.cs file to TRUE (as shown below) and still didn't work.  


namespace SoundtrackEditor
{
    [KSPAddon(KSPAddon.Startup.Instantly, true)]
    public class GuiManager : MonoBehaviour
    {// ☰ ∞ 
        // GUI window location and sizes.
        protected Rect mainWindowPos = new Rect(Screen.width / 10, Screen.height / 20f, 400f, 10f);
        protected Rect playbackWindowPos = new Rect((Screen.width / 2) - 115, Screen.height / 10, 230f, 10f);
        protected Rect playlistWindowPos = new Rect((Screen.width / 2) - 115, Screen.height / 20, 400f, 10f);
        protected Rect audioPreviewWindowPos = new Rect((Screen.width / 2) - 115, Screen.height / 20, 400f, 10f);
        protected Rect editorWindowPos = new Rect(Screen.width / 6, 50, (Screen.width / 1.5f), Screen.height / 1.15f);

        // GUI visibility toggles.
        private static bool _allUIHidden = false;
        private bool _mainWindowVisible = true; // TODO: Persist this value for startup
        private bool _situationVisible = true;
        private bool _playbackControlsVisible = true;
        private bool _playlistGuiVisible = true;
        private bool _audioPreviewGuiVisible = true;
        private bool _editorGuiVisible = true;

        // Addon toolbar
        private static string _appImageFile = "SoundtrackEditor/Images/sted";
        internal bool Tooltip = false;
        private static ApplicationLauncherButton appButton = null;

        private string _previousSeekPosition = string.Empty; // Last seek position of the audio player's seek control.
        private bool _muted = false;
        private bool _playerTracksExpanded = false;
        private Vector2 _playlistScrollPosition = Vector2.zero;
        private Vector2 _tracksScrollPosition = Vector2.zero;
        private Dictionary<string, bool> _expandedPlaylists = new Dictionary<string, bool>();
        private Vector2 _audioDBScrollPosition = Vector2.zero;
        private Dictionary<string, bool> _expandedDbItems = new Dictionary<string, bool>();
        private List<AudioLoader.AudioFileInfo> _audioFileList;
        public AudioSource PreviewSpeaker;

 

I know next to nothing about coding, but is there something else I could try? This mod has become one of those "why isn't this in the base game?" type mods IMO.

@Atreyu How did you install it? If by CKAN then I think that's the problem as it only unpacks files to GameData/SoundtrackEditor directory and there are 6 more directories to unpack. I've downloaded from curse and unpacked it manually and it worked (GUI, music, playlists - all there, although not playing always, but I think it's another problem).

On 10/15/2017 at 5:12 AM, Locusi said:

@Atreyu How did you install it? If by CKAN then I think that's the problem as it only unpacks files to GameData/SoundtrackEditor directory and there are 6 more directories to unpack. I've downloaded from curse and unpacked it manually and it worked (GUI, music, playlists - all there, although not playing always, but I think it's another problem).

In your KSP root directory this mod also needs /Soundtracks and /Music. It used to all be inside /GameData/SoundtrackEditor according to @pizzaoverhead's release notes. I think that's cleaner, but not my call.

Manual install includes /Source but you don't need it. Inside of /Music pizzaoverhead includes some folders for organizing the music but this is for human convenience -- STED doesn't care as long as the music file (go with .ogg -- .mp3 support is baahroken) is in /Music.

 

As for RAM usage, seems mo' music mo' problems. Commented in the source code, pizza has notes-to-self about future plans to only load music files that appear in the user's playlists.cfg and ditch the rest, but this is another WIP feature.

Edited October 17, 2017 by Brendan_
I did in fact download it from CKAN and my root directory has the /Music file but no /Soundtrack. I'll try reinstalling it via Curse once I get back from work.

On 17.10.2017 at 6:09 AM, Brendan_ said:

In your KSP root directory this mod also needs /Soundtracks and /Music. It used to all be inside /GameData/SoundtrackEditor according to @pizzaoverhead's release notes. I think that's cleaner, but not my call.

As for RAM usage, seems mo' music mo' problems. Commented in the source code, pizza has notes-to-self about future plans to only load music files that appear in the user's playlists.cfg and ditch the rest, but this is another WIP feature.

Thanks for explanation @Brendan_

I've checked again today, unpacked only Gamedata/SoundTrackEditor, Music and Playlists (I'm lazy and like to use what is already there :-) ) and all seems to work. I don't need Soundtracks in root KSP directory.

Only one thing I don't like is this warning:

To eradicate it I copy from Soundtrack Editor archive KSP_x64_Data/libmpg123-0.dll to KSP/KSP_x64_Data (I run KSP_x64 on Windows) and I can add and hear mp3 with no problems. I'll check how it works for a longer period of time :-)

And I have great request for @pizzaoverhead - could you please rearrange all files/directories to be in Gamedata/SoundTrackEditor/*? If it's in root KSP directory it breaks CKAN spec compatibility (https://github.com/KSP-CKAN/CKAN/blob/master/Spec.md): 

install_to: The target location where the matched file or directory should be installed.
Valid values for this entry are GameData, Ships, Ships/SPH(v1.12), Ships/VAB(v1.12), Ships/(v1.16), Ships/(v1.16), Tutorial, Scenarios (v1.14) and GameRoot (which should be used sparingly, if at all).
A path to a given subfolder location can be specified only under GameData (v1.2); for example: GameData/MyMod/Plugins. The client must check this path and abort the install if any attempts to traverse up directories are found (eg: GameData/../Example).
Subfolder paths under a matched directory will be preserved, but directories will only be created when installing to GameData, Tutorial, or Scenarios.

I know that maybe you don't care for CKAN, but there are users using it and really happy with it.

Many thanks for this mod and for your support.

Luke.

Edited October 21, 2017 by Locusi
@Locusi Anything placed into Gamedata is loaded into memory. Since soundtracks can achieve 300mb+, root KSP directory seems better suited and matches the "use sparingly" policy.

Soundtrack Editor 4.4 is now available. This is mainly a bugfix release to get things back on track:

  • Added pre-launch ambience similar to the Space Centre.
  • Fixed non-numeric input being allowed for numeric fields.
  • Fixed "Pause On Game Pause" not working.
  • Fixed current track resetting on situation change that didn't change the playlist.
  • Fixed max/min velocity/altitude settings not working.
  • Fixed error on saving new playlists in some cases.
  • Fixed issues with nearby vessels check.

There are likely still some issues left. If you find any, make a post detailing how I can reproduce it, including the playlist.cfg and output_log.txt files as appropriate.

Enjoy!

Yeeah! I'm going to check it out right now.

I am using @Brendan_ release of SE and suddenly @pizzaoverhead pushes 4.4!

I, like, fall off the chair!!

Congrats on the new release  I'll have to find time to look at my Jahzzar music release again and try and add some of the missing features! I don't know how soon it'll be though considering I only have around one hour of free time at my computer now most days...

@Avera9eJoe I will be releasing my own music pak soon. I will include two playlists - for my pack only (pure) and my pack mixed with yours (Jahzzar). This is playlist only, users will need to get your pack seperately for this to work, so its like "compatibility patch".

Will be looking forward to your updated awesome package!
OK! Kerbal Music Extension - 23 music tracks for Soundtrack Editor UP! Video demo included! Enjoy!!

@pizzaoverhead @brendan It looks like the famous "no craft - no music" bug is unfixed in stock 4.4... I have encountered it several times, once in mainmenu, at least three times in "Flying"+"Situation:any"+"Atmosphere:yes" which is primary list in Jahhzar music pack for atmospheric (below 70km) activity.

Edited November 28, 2017 by Kerbal101
I am sometimes always almost blind...

5 hours ago, Kerbal101 said:

@pizzaoverhead @brendan It looks like the famous "no craft - no music" bug is unfixed in stock 4.4... I have encountered it several times, once in mainmenu, at least three times in "Flying"+"Situation:any"+"Atmosphere:yes" which is primary list in Jahhzar music pack for atmospheric (below 70km) activity.

Hi @Kerbal101, can you include the playlist.cfg, save file and output_log.txt for this? I'd like to get this one solved once and for all. If you have a process that reliably makes this happen, that would be a great help too. Thanks!

@pizzaoverhead Hello!
I explored a bit, and it looks a bit different - music does get stuck, but it retains the current playlist.
You can hit previous/next buttons and it will then play next track, but will freeze again. Also it rewinds the position of "position tracker" a few seconds back from the very end.
 

In 4.3 stock, freeze was permanent, and STED will also loose the pointer to current playlist.

The moment is completely random and not dependent on save game, - start easy sandbox in 1.3.1 , grab "Kerbal 1" rocket, travel to low orbit and let it fly for several tracks.
I am using KMX+Jahzzar with KMX+Jahzzar playlist.


I am on linux and this is what I found in tail of KSP.log when I got that thing above: https://pastebin.com/zSyCF3B6

Also, I found just now that hitting "STOP" key suddenly fixes the issue?!!
In the log that moment happened after taking screenshots, after 18:47 19:00

 

Btw I found conflict between stock "prelaunch" and jahzzar "flying" playlists, so I will update kmx soon with playlist change, but this is not part of the bug.

Edited November 28, 2017 by Kerbal101

Quick question,

I noticed that all the stock soundtracks for KSP are preloaded and previewable in SE. All of my Ogg files that I've placed in the Music folder are not pre-loaded and not preview able. I've noticed a hang-up when selecting my spacecraft from the tracking station where the "space" music does not load(it does for amoment while loading the scene but stops once scene is loaded) while in space. 

Being someone who has extra memory to spare(64gigs ram) I'd like to preload all the custom tracks I want to use so that SE has no problem switching to tracks on the fly, is this possible?

@SwissSpace93 Happy new year!

So... I have some hacky solution: you could create a new ogg sound file using an editor, such as Audacity. Select "Insert Silence" from menu and create 8 minutes of silence. Export this file as "silence.ogg" to your "Music" directory (not in Gamedata).

Then you will need to edit your playlist file, and do two things:
- insert "silence.ogg" into playlists you want (track = silence ).
- deactivate shuffle option ( shuffle = False )

Its hacky, because you need shuffle deactivated, or you may get ... random amount of silence.
